snippet.textDisplay: Let's be openly blunt here. The overall performance of Arsenal was pointedly rubbish. Arsenal games are not for the faint hearted. One needs to have 911 on speed dial!! The performance of this team is one of the worst ever......and I've been watching The Gunners for a long time. Last night's game is one of those that leaves you asking, "What happened?" because you can't  explain how, playing so badly, we could have won! Ozil, Xhaka were dreadful and so were much of the team. But win, we did. I hope that doesn't  mask the load of work that still needs doing. And, NO!!!, Freddie Ljungberg's not the man to take us forward. At least now I can recall when we last won. Please let it not be a flash in the pan. Reluctantly I say, "Well done ".

snippet.textDisplay: Dreadful game between a bad WHU and a slightly better Arsenal. WH should have been 3 up by half time if it were not for Leno and the fact they didn't have a forward on the pitch that could score a goal. This result fools no one - but respect to Pepe (who I have criticised) for his goal and general play. Now do it against a team that doesn't allow you the freeedom of the park. For periods I was shocked at how comical these two teams were. Bad passing, bad shooting, bad defending - just plain bad. But credit AFC they dug out a win but the table does refelct where these two teams are at right now and I fully expect Man City to give Arsenal a right good walloping.
